description.plain:
“New Year, Same Sad” is Eleventh Cassette’s 2019 playlist for new releases and also new discoveries from former years. The playlist will contain a variety of artists and genres, but mainly alternative rock/pop and post/metal hardcore.

Feel free to follow it throughout the year if you want to discover new music!

search_results.lyrics:
Spring to Life Lyrics[Verse 1]
You keep calling same time each week
I thought it blew over, but this hurricane beats
I cling onto every word you speak
What do I, do I feel?

[Pre-Chorus]
Why do I let this phase me?
You're sick of all my maybes

[Chorus]
Photographs hung in my mind
I keep them up just to be polite
Now we're moving out of time
That's when we both spring to life
Spring to life
Spring to life
That's when we both spring to life
[Verse 2]
I stopped smoking, cleaned up my room
Did all the things I said I'd do
When I was so caught up on you
What do I feel?
What do I feel?

[Chorus]
Photographs hung in my mind
I keep them up just to be polite
Now we're moving out of time
That's when we both spring to lifе
Stumblin' 'round my head at night
Always leaving things behind
Now wе're moving out of time
That's when we both spring to life
Spring to life
Spring to life
That's when we both spring to life

[Instrumental Outro]You might also likeEmbed

description.plain:
“New Year, Same Sad” is Eleventh Cassette’s 2019 playlist for new releases and also new discoveries from former years. The playlist will contain a variety of artists and genres, but mainly alternative rock/pop and post/metal hardcore.

Feel free to follow it throughout the year if you want to discover new music!

description.plain: I had only just finished high school when I went into write Hunger, and I guess I struggled quite a lot with Tall Poppy Syndrome in the end years of high school. I felt like I was so invested in this music career and nobody would really take me seriously and it really hurt me, I guess I was just looking to know that my friends were proud of me or excited for what I was doing but I never really got that and I did struggle with accepting that people can become mean or nasty if they feel threatened or jealous about what you are achieving. It’s a song about Tall Poppy Syndrome and I feel like it’s such a relatable song because it is everywhere, not just within the music industry but almost every single career path.

What you want is what I need
 But I was there to help you breathe
There’s only so many times you can try to help someone out and try and help them to get to where they want to be, but it’s only them that can help themselves!

What you want is what I’ve had
 But it’s turned into something bad

This relates so closely to tall poppy syndrome – I was achieving things that some other people weren’t but were striving towards and I think feelings got involved and it just turned into an awful situation of jealousy and longing for what somebody else has.

Keys can’t copy
 My wrists break for the night
You can copy people and want what they have so badly that you ruin yourself and relationships along the way.

I sawed my legs right off
 To watch you walk by

This is probably one of my favourite lines of the song, it is pretty much just a way of saying I stopped doing things so you could be happy, or I turned down opportunities so that I could keep the peace in a friendship

You’re kind of hungry for it
 Yeah, take a bite
If you want something bad enough or are hungry for something, go and get it.

Why
 Do we feed off the same line

I feel like when you’re sharing the same goals and aspirations with someone, it could easily affect friendships/relationships etc. So this lyric is pointing out that yes we are doing the same thing or ‘feeding off the same line’ but try not to let the things like jealousy, envy etc. get in the way of what is real.

The difference is it’s taking
 Too much of your time
You can ponder for so long on unimportant and silly things that it can eventually take up way to much of your time and energy when it could be focused elsewhere.

And all the lines are changing
 Whatever helps you sleep at night

A huge thing for me in high school was having to realize that not everyone is going to understand what you’re doing or care about what you’re doing, and sometimes they’ll act certain ways or say certain things you don’t agree with and this line pretty much means that life is changing and people are changing but sometimes people do what helps them feel better about themselves no matter the cost.

Seemed to like the woodwork of the place where I lay
 Got no signs that you tried

This line pretty much means that people can love and want the things that you have but they will never achieve those thing if they don’t try their best, things don’t come easy to most people, you make your own luck.
